fields.name: El Caballito
fields.description: At El Caballito Tequila y Tacos we serve street-style Mexican cuisine along with a robust selection of over 100 Tequilas and craft cocktails in downtown Toronto.

fields.name: Los Colibris
fields.description: Los Colibrís, meaning “the hummingbirds”, is Toronto’s first upscale Mexican restaurant that features exceptional hospitality, white linen service, and authentic world class Mexican cuisine by Executive Chef Elia Herrera.

fields.name: Grace O'Malleys
fields.description: At Grace O'Malley's the story of Grainne Ni Mhaille, or Granuaile (Anglicized as Grace O'Malley, Grany Malley), reads like the most brazen and unlikely sort of adventure fiction, but thereU+FFE2s history as well as myth in the legend of the Irish noblewoman who led a band of 200 sea-raiders from the coast of Galway in the sixteenth century.

fields.name: Bellwoods Brewery
fields.description: Bellwoods began as a small brewery, and pub in downtown Toronto. We officially opened our doors to the public in April 2012, and spent the majority of the first few years working increasingly unhealthy schedules to avoid running out of beer. Spoiler alert: we often failed.

fields.name: 360 Restaurant
fields.description: 360 The Restaurant at the CN Tower, one of Toronto's finest, features unforgettable food combined with a magnificent revolving view of Toronto more than 351 metres (1,151 ft) below. 360 offers market-fresh cuisine, featuring regional ingredients to ensure an incomparable culinary experience.360 The Restaurant at the CN Tower, one of Toronto's finest, features unforgettable food combined with a magnificent revolving view of Toronto more than 351 metres (1,151 ft) below. 360 offers market-fresh cuisine, featuring regional ingredients to ensure an incomparable culinary experience.

fields.name: Salt Wine bar
fields.description: Located at the top of the Ossington strip, Salt wine bar offers a modern progressive approach to Iberian/Canadian tapas. Salt is a bustling, cozy, communal tapas bar with great energy. Our guests enjoy artisanal cheeses, Iberian charcuterie and an excellent variety of small plate dishes. Chef Dave Kemp is strongly committed to using seasonal and local products whenever possible. Our cellar contains an extensive list of Portuguese and Spanish wines which complement each and every dish.

fields.name: Pai
fields.description: Nuit & Jeff Regular's casual Northern Thai spot serving dishes like salted crab & papaya salad.

fields.name: Khao San Road
fields.description: Lively eatery adorned with patterned tiles & colourful flags serving classic Thai curries & noodles.

fields.name: Elephant & Castle
fields.description: Chain with a British pub feel serving fish 'n' chips, American classics & beers on tap.
